"1. Once ANC is activated, the LED indicator at the lower left-sided headphones will be constantly on, it shows remaining battery level： Green Light: Battery Level >80% Yellow Light: Battery Level 10%-80% Red Light: Battery Level <10%
2. Operating Time： ANC OFF, mid volume and fiil logo light off： 50 hours ANC ON, mid volume and fiil logo light on： 32 hours
3. The LED indicator goes off after battery is fully charged.
4. Once battery runs out, the ANC is not available but Music can still be listened with headphones."

"1. Short press the button at the lower right-sided, the LED indicator shows remaining battery level； Green Light: Battery Level >80% Yellow Light: Battery Level 20%-80% Red Light: Battery Level 10%-20% Flickering Red Light: Battery Level <10%

3. Once battery runs out, the Bluetooth and ANC are not available but Music can still be listened with wired mode.

Heart rate is the most convenient index for assessing exercise-induced fatigue.

"When the body is functioning normally, your heart rate when you've just woken up early in the morning and are lying still is relatively stable and very close to your resting heart rate. Accumulated fatigue can be noticed when an individual has exercised, had a good night's sleep, and then early the next morning has a noticeably increased heart rate which may be accompanied by sore muscles and joints. If this increases for a few days in a row, the intensity of exercise should be reduced."
"Perform test in the early morning when you've just woken up, within five minutes of getting up."
